1.	Give average of the total fare.

select avg(total_fare) "Total Fare's Average"
FROM ticket_header;

2.	Give the total collection of fare.

select sum(total_fare)
from ticket_header;

3.	Which bus runs for minimum distance?

SELECT route_id, route_no, distance
FROM route_header
WHERE distance = (SELECT MIN(distance) FROM route_header);

4.	Give the total number of people who have traveled so far group by ticket number.

 select ticket_no,sum(adult+children)
from ticket_header
group by ticket_no;

5.	Find out total fare for routes with same origin.

SELECT origin, sum(total_fare)"Total Fare"
from ticket_header
group by origin;

6.	Find out total fare for routes with origin as madras.

 select origin, sum(total_fare)
from ticket_header
where origin = "Madras";

7.	Calculate average fare for each ticket.

 select ticket_no, total_fare/(adult+children)
from ticket_header;

8.	Find out details of fleets that run on route number 33 or 25.

 select *
from fleet_header
where route_id in (select route_id
from route_header
where route_no in (33,25));

9.	Count how many male or female passengers have travelled till now.

select sex, count(ticket_no)
from ticket_detail
group by sex;

10.	Count total number of routes for each category except category 02.

 select cat_code, count(route_no)
from route_header
group by cat_code
having cat_code not in (02);


11.	Find out place names for which nonstop buses run.

select ph.place_name
from place_header ph
inner join route_detail rd
on ph.place_id = rd.place_id
where rd.nonstop = "n";

select place_name
from place_header
where place_id in (select place_id
from route_detail where nonstop = "n");

12.	Find out details of tickets from ticket header having more than one passenger.


 SELECT *
FROM ticket_header
WHERE (adult + children) > 1;


13.	Find out details of route having category code same as category code of a route having maximum distance.

select *
from route_header
where cat_code = (select cat_code
from route_header
where distance = (select max(distance)
from route_header));
